Description: I’m putting up for sale 5 of my Ibanez guitars. Check my other listings or the last picture. I got a little bit carried away with the gear acquisitions, so now will have to sell the ones that I don’t play. This listing is for Ibanez S520EX in satin black. It’s in good condition. This is the thinnest guitar I’ve ever had. See the picture of it next to regular RG. The Floyd rose was upgraded to the Jackson branded one. Pick ups also were upgraded to I believe hexbuckers(?) definitely better than the stock ones. Predator inlay on the 12th fret, Wizard neck, made in Korea!! It has been painted not too long ago, so there are no scratches whatsoever. The paint job isn’t exactly professional thou. Check the pictures if you can see what I mean. Missing tremolo cover on the back Here’s some info from web: The S520EX is an S series solid body electric guitar model introduced by Ibanez in 2005. It was initially produced in Korea and then later in Indonesia. The S520EX features a thin, sculpted mahogany body bolted to a maple Wizard II neck with a 22-fret rosewood fingerboard with binding and claw scratch inlays only at the twelfth fret. Components include a pair of Ibanez Infinity covered humbucking pickups and a ZR ball-bearing pivot double locking tremolo bridge with a ZPS2 tuning stabilizer. US only. Will ship within 2 days of receiving payment. There are two shipping options and free local pick up if you are in NYC area.
Title: Ibanez S520ex S Series Black Predator Inlay Floyd Rose Slim Made In Korea
